column5: Yeah, the more and more I look the more I realize it's a black crappie.  It's bigger then most bass I catch
If you guys caught one that big...would you keep or release it?
Release it, what's the point of keeping it?  All the big crappies are females.  Gotta let them reproduce.
If you guys caught one that big...would you keep or release it?  Ide take a ton of pics and release it, but it would be getting replicated for sure...

Yep same here?  Billm, yes, this black crappie must have been confused and though it was a largemouth?  I can hardly believe a crappie got that big!  My pb is 14.25" and I never weighed it but id guessunder 1.5lbs???
We get some nice ones down here, but this on on a whole different level.
Hi Manitoubass 2,  Did you or friend actually caught this crappie? Was it in Canada and when was it?  Thanks!
I think I know a couple of lakes that hold some monsters.  Late fall will tell.
It was posted on facebook by an angler in the US  I got it from ron lidner and he said they were trying to track down the angler(whatever that means)
19.25" 4.25lb(alleged) black crappie
Jeez, now that's a slab!
Wow, and i thought my 1 lbers were big lol.
Wow!
Big slab, the weight seems about right for a healthy one that length.
Ate a bass.  Geesh!  That's a catch.
That looks like a white crappie to me, which get way bigger then the black crappie we get up here.  Imagine pulling that thing in? lol!
Shenanigans!  That's as big as my biggest bass this year!
I wonder if that's the same fish that Spiel posted in "Fishing News" March 29, 2010.
Def a black crappie, def a good one
Oh my!!  That's a hog!!!
WOW  awesome fish.I wanna get me some crappie.
Never seen that pic roy, maybe?  I seen this posted by ron lidner last night on facecrack

I wonder if that's the same fish that Spiel posted in "Fishing News" March 29, 2010. Don't think so. Here's a pic of the guy that Spiel posted:  http://www.swankboys.com/2010/05/did-you-hear-about-4-12-pound-crappie_16.html
That last one has been thrown at the camera....LOL  First one looks legit though. Cameras are funny things when you mess with perspective.
Way to stay on top of things Dara    I mean Dana.  Both HUGE slabters
Cheese n Crepes that's huge!
Even with the hero pose in the second picture, the first one looks bigger
Was it caught in Ontario?
I love what you can do with Photoshop.
Ill look to see if I can find the post.  Im pretty sure it said stateside

Thats one heck of a photoshop job. Not saying it isnt possible but if thats the case someone took alot of time. Just look at the tail alone  A photoshopped pic usually gives up a clue or two, I see none in this pic
I am guessing a black crappie.
If that's a black crappie, I'll eat my hat!  I can't get over how big that thing is, lol!!
That's certainly a black, better start marinating that hat bill!  Its .75 lbs short of a world record if its truly 4.25 pounds...true monster
